      {
        "id": "e41ca0abd544fda4b5751782373f9e089b6611c4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-05-16 12:42:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nNote that sdnc/core/rootpom/pom.xml (parent of all top-level pom.xmls in sdnc) depends on odlparent, not features-parent.  I believe to use this placeholder, we would need to define separate parent poms for ODL features vs other types of plugins that we support.  I would support such a change for the end of year release, but for now am concerned this could break our builds.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "c711cb26a3ab533a560a05b3ba990685ea040453",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-05-16 13:00:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Note that sdnc/core/rootpom/pom.xml (parent of all top-level pom.xmls in sdnc) depends on odlparent, not features-parent.\n\nRight, and ODL parent import all odlparent-artifacts making them available. https://github.com/opendaylight/odlparent/blob/release/boron-sr1/odlparent/pom.xml#L138-L144 \n\n> I believe to use this placeholder, we would need to define separate parent poms for ODL features \n\nActually, the right approach would be to move those feature bundles to use feature-parent directly. But I'm trying to address this with digestible iteration.\n\n> am concerned this could break our builds.\n\nThe build is passing, so I'm not sure to understand your concern?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "1ed0feffe13a336436899c06ac2d9c579919d9d2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-05-16 19:36:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nit compiles okay, but if you take a look inside the jar it generates, the {{VERSION}} is not being expanded in the features.xml file - so it wouldn't install properly.  I did a local compile and verified that myself",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
